<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-05-08T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-05-08T14:00:00-05:00" n="650" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d650">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.74/231: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-05-08T15:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">May 8, 1922—3
                                        p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>114. Your telegram No. 114 of March 24, 5 p.m. Some time ago the
                            Department communicated to Mr. Schwerin, who has been ill, the substance
                            of that telegram. With his engineers he is in New York conducting
                            negotiations for traffic agreements and arranging other matters which
                            are necessary incidental to the carrying out of the contract of the
                            Federal Telegraph Company. Exact information will be cabled to you as
                            soon as the Department can obtain it from Mr. Schwerin.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>